:R-HSA-9020956  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0070106 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Interleukin-27 (IL27) is a heterodimeric cytokine that contains Epstein-Barr virus–induced gene 3 (EBI3) and IL27p28 (IL27). It signals through a receptor composed of Interleukin-6 receptor subunit beta (IL6ST, gp130), which is utilized by many cytokines, and Interleukin-27 receptor subunit alpha (IL27RA, WSX-1, TCCR) (Yoshida & Hunter 2015)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Interleukin-27 signaling" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: van de Vosse, Esther, 2017-05-12" , "Reviewed: Narazaki, M, Tanaka, M, 2015-11-09" , "Authored: Duenas, Corina, 2016-12-02" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Jupe, S, 2009-11-24" , "Edited: Jupe, Steve, 2017-11-09" ;
